                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>There is no columetric layout of text</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r #8r #16r #24v #43r"/> (haräg);
                  <locus target="#35v #43r #49r #58r #64v #69v #79r #85r #100r #115v #122r #154r"/> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#128v #140v"/> (multiple full stops and lines of red and black dots).
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iiir(ecto)"/>": Excerpt from the <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT3575Mashaf"/> for the Night Hours, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰዓታት፡ ሌሊት፡</foreign>, written in purple ink
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኵሎሙ፡ ሠራዊተ፡ መላእክት፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#157r #157v #158 #158v"/>: scrawls and lists of names, written in blue and red ink, and pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecot) #ii v(erso)"/>": scrawls and pentrials
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iiiv(erso)"/>": blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#64v"/>: the mid-point of the Psalms is marked with a line of alternating red and black dots
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#156v"/>, bottom of column two: scrawls in purple ink and pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 28
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 does not contain the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#74v #96v #103r #105v #108v"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#101r"/>);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#45v #95v #112r"/>).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
